# JavaScript Style

## No inline return

Do not put `return` on the same line as a condition. Use a block with the return on its own line.

```javascript
// BAD
if (stateLoaded) return;
if (env > 0) return env;
if (prices.length === 0) return null;

// GOOD
if (stateLoaded) {
  return;
}
if (env > 0) {
  return env;
}
if (prices.length === 0) {
  return null;
}
```

## Project structure

- **config/** – Constants and paths only.
- **lib/** – Shared state and pure helpers (format, state).
- **clients/** – External API wrappers (Bybit, Telegram); no app logic.
- **jobs/** – Use cases / orchestration (e.g. P2P check).

Use `src/config`, `src/lib`, `src/clients`, `src/jobs` for imports; avoid barrel files that mix concerns.
